Fortunately, the store sells horseshoes of all colors under the sun and Valera has enough money to buy any four of them. However, in order to save the money, he would like to spend as little money as possible, so you need to help Valera and determine what is the minimum number of horseshoes he needs to buy to wear four horseshoes of different colors to a party.\n\n    Input\n    The input contains four integers s1 , s2 , s3 , s4 (1 \u2264 s1 , s2 , s3 , s4 \u2264 10^9 ) \u2014 the colors of horseshoes Valera has. However, in order to save the money, he would like to spend as little money as possible, so you need to help Valera and determine what is the minimum number of horseshoes he needs to buy to wear four horseshoes of different colors to a party.\n\n    Input\n    The input contains four integers s1 , s2 , s3 , s4 (1 \u2264 s1 , s2 , s3 , s4 \u2264 10^9 ) \u2014 the colors of horseshoes Valera has. Consider all possible colors indexed with integers.\n\n    Output\n    Output a single integer \u2014 the minimum number of horseshoes Valera needs to buy.\n*/\n/*@ logic integer amountOfDifferentNumbers(integer a, integer b, integer c, integer d) =\n    1 + (int) (a != b) + (int) (a != c && b != c) + (int) (a != d && b != d && c != d);\n */\n\n/*@ predicate IsValidSolution(integer a, integer b, integer c, integer d, integer out) =\n    out + amountOfDifferentNumbers(a, b, c, d) >= 4;\n*/\n\n/*@ predicate ExistsSmallerSolution(integer a, integer b, integer c, integer d, integer out) =\n    \\exists integer unique_colors;\n    0 <= unique_colors && unique_colors + amountOfDifferentNumbers(a, b, c, d) >= 4 &&\n        unique_colors < out;\n*/\n\n/*@\n    requires \\valid(out);\n    requires 1 <= a <= 1000000000;\n    requires 1 <= b <= 1000000000;\n    requires 1 <= c <= 1000000000;\n    requires 1 <= d <= 1000000000;\n    assigns *out;\n    ensures IsValidSolution(a, b, c, d, *out);\n    ensures !ExistsSmallerSolution(a, b, c, d, *out);\n*/\nvoid minimumHorseshoesNeeded(int a, int b, int c, int d, int *out) {\n    int ab_diff = (a != b);\n    int ac_diff = (a != c);\n    int ad_diff = (a != d);\n    int bc_diff = (b != c);\n    int bd_diff = (b != d);\n    int cd_diff = (c != d);\n\n    int diff_count = 1 + ab_diff + (ac_diff && bc_diff) + (ad_diff && bd_diff && cd_diff);\n    \n    if (diff_count < 4) {\n        *out = 4;\n    } else {\n        *out = diff_count;\n    }\n}\n",

Fortunately, the store sells horseshoes of all colors under the sun and Valera has enough money to buy any four of them. However, in order to save the money, he would like to spend as little money as possible, so you need to help Valera and determine what is the minimum number of horseshoes he needs to buy to wear four horseshoes of different colors to a party.\n\n    Input\n    The input contains four integers s1 , s2 , s3 , s4 (1 \u2264 s1 , s2 , s3 , s4 \u2264 10^9 ) \u2014 the colors of horseshoes Valera has. Consider all possible colors indexed with integers.\n\n    Output\n    Output a single integer \u2014 the minimum number of horseshoes Valera needs to buy.\n*/\n/*@ logic integer amountOfDifferentNumbers(integer a, integer b, integer c, integer d) =\n    1 + (int) (a != b) + (int) (a != c && b != c) + (int) (a != d && b != d && c != d);\n */\n\n/*@ predicate IsValidSolution(integer a, integer b, integer c, integer d, integer out) =\n    out + amountOfDifferentNumbers(a, b, c, d) >= 4;\n*/\n\n/*@ predicate ExistsSmallerSolution(integer a, integer b, integer c, integer d, integer out) =\n    \\exists integer unique_colors;\n    0 <= unique_colors && unique_colors + amountOfDifferentNumbers(a, b, c, d) >= 4 &&\n        unique_colors < out;\n*/\n\n/*@\n    requires \\valid(out);\n    requires 1 <= a <= 1000000000;\n    requires 1 <= b <= 1000000000;\n    requires 1 <= c <= 1000000000;\n    requires 1 <= d <= 1000000000;\n    assigns *out;\n    ensures IsValidSolution(a, b, c, d, *out);\n    ensures !ExistsSmallerSolution(a, b, c, d, *out);\n*/\nvoid minimumHorseshoesNeeded(int a, int b, int c, int d, int *out) {\n    int ab_diff = (a != b);\n    int ac_diff = (a != c);\n    int ad_diff = (a != d);\n    int bc_diff = (b != c);\n    int bd_diff = (b != d);\n    int cd_diff = (c != d);\n\n    *out = 4 - ab_diff - (ac_diff && bc_diff) - (ad_diff && bd_diff) - (ab_diff && ac_diff && ad_diff);\n}\n",

However, in order to save the money, he would like to spend as little money as possible, so you need to help Valera and determine what is the minimum number of horseshoes he needs to buy to wear four horseshoes of different colors to a party.\n\n    Input\n    The input contains four integers s1 , s2 , s3 , s4 (1 \u2264 s1 , s2 , s3 , s4 \u2264 10^9 ) \u2014 the colors of horseshoes Valera has.
